    • Constructor Detail

      • SqsConsumer

        public SqsConsumer(SqsConsumerBuilder<T> builder)
        Adds a consumer for a specific SQS Queue. Once a consumer is started, the handler will be called from a thread-pool to process messages. It is safe to use blocking calls in the handler as this will not impact performance if a sufficient number of `workerThreads` are configured in the SqsConsumerManager. Only one consumer is normally needed per SQS Queue. A single long-polling request is always in-flight for each consumer in addition to the load-balanced requests configured in the `SqsConsumerManager`.
